Actor Williams Uchemba has given a ‘little Push Gift’ for his wife after the arrival of their first child. On Sunday, February 13, the entertainer and his wife Brunella welcomed their first child, Chikamara Isabella Uchemba. Taking to his Instagram page to announce the news, the overwhelmed new dad shared a video in which he recounted the pregnancy journey while he also expressed affection for the newest addition in the family. He wrote: “Welcome home, Chikamara Isabella Uchembah. Thank you for fulfilling my greatest desire of being a Dad. I can’t explain how you make me feel but it’s been so surreal. I love you.”   Burna Boy reaches 200m streams on Boomplay, gets honour     2Baba, wife to star in Netflix first all-African reality…     Abba Kyari’s arrest: Obi Cubana trends on Twitter   - Advertisement - Two days after, the film star surprised his wife with a ‘push gift’, a brand new Mercedes Benz GLC 300 4MATIC for making his dream of becoming a dad a reality. He shared a video that captured him while he was at the car showroom to the point he presented the luxurious gift to his wife. Uchemba wrote: “A little Push Gift for all the stress you went through these past nine months trying to bring @kamarauchemba into the world. “From the sleepless nights to the back pains and how standing up became your favorite sleeping position. “Thank you for making me a father to the most beautiful baby I’ve set my eyes on, you are indeed a superwoman and your strength can’t be matched. I LOVE YOU. “And a big shout out to all the awaiting mothers and mothers out there, you guys are the real MVP.” SPONSORED